    <Object Type="Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.Design.StaticTextControl, Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.CommonControls, Version=17.3.40.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" Name="StaticTextControl2" Children="Controls" ControlName="Static Text">
      <Property Name="Name">StaticTextControl2</Property>
      <Property Name="Size">555, 104</Property>
      <Property Name="Location">19, 129</Property>
      <Property Name="BackColor">HighlightText</Property>
      <Property Name="Text">The generated voltages are used as follows:

Channel 01 generates a voltage depending on the position of the 'Analog Dimmable LED' slider on the CANoe panel.
This voltage is used to dim an LED on the DUT.

Channel 02 generates a voltage depending on the position of the 'Counter Speed' slider on the CANoe panel.
This voltage is used to calculate the counter speed of the 4-bit counter on the DUT.
The voltage range is 0..5V, the counter speed range is 2..20Hz.
</Property>
    </Object>
